President Obama has declared a major disaster in South Dakota and authorized federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts from a severe winter storm that occurred from January 20-26, 2010. The federal funding will be available to state and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected areas include various counties and reservations within South Dakota. In addition, federal funding will also be provided for hazard mitigation measures throughout the state. Nancy M. Casper has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected area. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations and aid. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.